                            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                A clean home is essential for creating a relaxing and organized living space, but maintaining that cleanliness can often feel like a never-ending chore. One of the best ways to stay on top of cleaning is by creating a weekly cleaning routine that fits your lifestyle. A consistent cleaning schedule not only makes your home more inviting but also helps reduce stress and prevent clutter from accumulating.
                            </p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Set Realistic Goals for Your Weekly Routine</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The key to sticking with any cleaning routine is setting realistic goals. It’s easy to get overwhelmed if you try to do everything at once, so it’s important to break down tasks into smaller, manageable steps.</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                <li><strong>Assess your needs:</strong> Prioritize high-traffic areas like the kitchen and bathroom.</li>
