                                <li><strong>Be flexible:</strong> If life gets busy, move tasks to the following week rather than giving up entirely.</li>
                            </ul>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Break Your Routine into Daily Tasks</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Breaking your weekly routine into daily tasks helps ensure that your cleaning routine becomes a habit. It prevents you from spending your entire weekend cleaning.</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                <li><strong>Daily tidying:</strong> Dedicate 10-15 minutes to quick tasks like making the bed and wiping kitchen counters.</li>
                                <li><strong>Focus on one task per day:</strong> Instead of cleaning everything, focus on just vacuuming Monday, dusting Tuesday, etc.</li>
                                <li><strong>Establish time blocks:</strong> Set aside a specific time each day to tackle your small cleaning task.</li>
                            </ul>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Create a Weekly Cleaning Checklist</h2>
